value.title: Pelosi: Trump diagnosis 'tragic,' hopefully leads to 'saner approach' to pandemic
value.excerpt: Speaker Nancy Pelosi said that President Trump’s COVID-19 diagnosis is “tragic” and “very sad,” but predictable, given his frequent contact with crowds.

value.title: AP PHOTOS: A busy week for Trump before positive virus test
value.excerpt: With just a month to go until the election, President Donald Trump had a busy schedule the days before he tested positive for the coronavirus, attending rallies, private fundraisers, a presidential debate and hosting events at the White House.

value.title: No one wore a mask during Trump debate prep, Chris Christie says
value.excerpt: Former N.J. Gov. Chris Christie revealed that no one in the room was wearing a mask when a small group of people gathered in the White House's map room on Monday to help prep President Trump for the first debate.

value.title: Mike Pence and his wife tested negative Friday morning.
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence announced Friday that he and his wife, Karen, had tested negative for the coronavirus, just hours after President Trump and the first lady announced they had both tested positive and were quarantining at the White House.

value.title: Boris Johnson wishes Trump 'speedy recovery' from COVID-19
value.excerpt: UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson wished President Trump a "speedy recovery" Friday, hours after he and First Lady Melania Trump tested positive for COVID-19.

value.title: In battleground Wisconsin, some Latinos feel ignored by Biden
value.excerpt: Cesar Hernandez says he has made thousands of phone calls since June urging Latinos in the battleground state of Wisconsin to support Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden.
